    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-06-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="435"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-06-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. White reports that he has applied in behalf of the Eisemanns for an
                    extension of leave to remain in Frankfort until April, 1903; <pb facs="0535"
                        n="455" xml:id="pg_455"/> that the brother at present in Germany declares
                    that they will then be ready to return to Boston.</p>
                <p>Mr. White has stated very fully to the foreign office the reasons for this
                    request.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
